Sentencas: A simple and cost-effective dip coating technique was successfully developed to fabricate NiO-YSZ anode substrates for cone-shaped anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Dip coating technique in fabrication of cone-shaped anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A single cell, NiO-YSZ/YSZ/LSM-YSZ, was assembled and tested to demonstrate the feasibility of the technique applied.
Titulo: Dip coating technique in fabrication of cone-shaped anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using humidified hydrogen (75 ml/min) as fuel and ambient air as oxidant, the maximum power density of the cell was 0.78 and 1.0 W/cm(2) at 800 and 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Dip coating technique in fabrication of cone-shaped anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The observed open-circuit voltages (OCV) was closed to the theoretical value and the scanning electron microscope (SEM) results revealed that the microstructures of the anode substrate and the cathode layer are porous and the electrolyte film is dense.
Titulo: Dip coating technique in fabrication of cone-shaped anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
